original: Hahne, Henning Olof Axel, kyrkoherde, Jämshögsby, f. 11/1/05 i Ishi, Shansi, N. Kina, av miss. Axel H. o. Anna Helena Watz. G. 1. 30’ m. Margit Sandborg, d. 45; 2. m. Margaretha Björnsson. Barn: Karin f. 31, Birgit 34, Staffan 36, Eva 37. — Stud:ex. i Sthlm 24, teol. fil. ex. 27, teol. kand. 28, prästv. f. Lunds stift 29. Past:-adj. i S. Rörum 29, v. kommin. i Ar-löv s. å., kommin. i Karlskrona 30, pred. v. ålderdomshemm. där 33, kyr-koh. i Jämishögsby sed. 42. Ordf. i Jämshögs kyrkofullm. o. folksk:styr.
translated: Hahne, Henning Olof Axel, pastor, Jämshögsby, born on January 11th, 1905 in Ishi, Shansi, North China, to missionary Axel H. and Anna Helena Watz. Married 1st in 1930 to Margit Sandborg who passed away in 1945, and 2nd to Margaretha Björnsson. Children: Karin born in 1931, Birgit in 1934, Staffan in 1936, and Eva in 1937. He completed his school-leaving certificate in Stockholm 1924, theology degree in 1927, theology candidate in 1928, and was ordained for the Lund diocese in 1929. He was an assistant pastor in Södra Rörum in 1929, a deputy minister in Arlöv the same year, a minister in Karlskrona in 1930, and a preacher at a nursing home there in 1933. He served as a pastor in Jämshögsby since 1942 and was a chairman of the Jämshögs parish council and elementary school board.

structured.name: Henning Olof Axel Hahne
structured.description: Henning Olof Axel Hahne was a Swedish pastor. He was born on January 11th, 1905 in Ishi, Shansi, North China to missionary Axel H. Hahne and Anna Helena Watz. He was married twice and had four children. He completed his school-leaving certificate in Stockholm 1924, theology degree in 1927, theology candidate in 1928, and was ordained for the Lund diocese in 1929. He served in various churches across Sweden before becoming a pastor in Jämshögsby in 1942. He also served as a chairman of Jämshögs parish council and elementary school board.
